decision_conditions:
Condition : 3 - Development shall not commence until a Working Method Statement, to incorporate a Construction Environmental Management Plan and an Air Quality Management Plan, has been submitted to and approved in writing by the Local Planning Authority to accommodate 
"           Parking of vehicles of site workers and visitors;
"           Loading and unloading of plant and materials;
"           Storage of construction plant and materials;
"           Wheel cleaning facilities
"           Control and monitoring of noise, vibration, dust, dirt, smell and other effluvia;
"           Control of surface water run-off.
"           Hours of operation
"           The erection and maintenance of security hoarding including decorative 
"           Wheel washing facilities 
"           A scheme for recycling/disposing of waste resulting from demolition and construction

The development shall not be implemented other than in accordance with the approved scheme, unless previously agreed in writing by the Local Planning Authority.

Reason: To ensure the safety of pedestrians and vehicles and the amenities of the surrounding area and to comply with the following Development Plan policies for Merton: policies T4 and T7 of the London Plan 2021, policy CS20 of Merton's Core Planning Strategy 2011 and policies DM D2, EP2, EP3, EP4 and DM T2 of Merton's Sites and Policies Plan 2014.
